We first note that one of the “Initial” transactions on 2023‑12‑31 already sets a book‐value for fixed assets at 5,000,000.00. Then later (on the same day) a fixed asset purchase transaction is recorded – with a row that has type “Fixed Assets Purchase” and an amount of 85,889.19. (In the sample set, a similar purchase increased the asset account.) 

Since the task does not require subtracting depreciation from the “fixed assets” cost (the sample solution did not subtract the depreciation either), we simply update the fixed asset balance by adding the fixed asset purchase amount to the initial value.

Thus, the ending fixed assets = 5,000,000.00 + 85,889.19 = 5,085,889.19.

